subject: p14744884
History: Evaluation of ET tube placement. Patient presenting hypoxic and intubated.
Findings: Portable AP chest radiograph. The ET tube is in appropriate position. NG tube courses below the diaphragm and terminates outside the field of view. Note is made of a right subclavian vein stent. There are low lung volumes and mild pulmonary edema. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax.
Impression: ET tube and NG tube are in appropriate position. Mild pulmonary edema.
